<item>
            <title>[FELIX-5147] Bundle Adapter auto configures class fields even if callbacks are used</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-5147</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When a bundle adapter is used with some callbacks (with or without a callback instance), then any fields in the adapter class with type=Bundle are auto-injected.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Normally, auto-configuration should be turned off when callbacks are used, exactly in the same manner it is done with regular service dependencies, or with service adapters.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
